From: Milk-V Vega OpenWrt port
Subject: [PATCH] riscv: disable ASID allocator on Nuclei UX608

UX608's SATP retains ASID-field writes but the TLB does not honour
ASIDs in matching, so the allocator causes stale TLB hits across MM
switches. Force the probe to report 0 ASID bits.

--- a/arch/riscv/mm/context.c
+++ b/arch/riscv/mm/context.c
@@ -234,6 +234,8 @@ static int __init asids_init(void)
 	csr_write(CSR_SATP, asid_bits);
 	asid_bits = (csr_read(CSR_SATP) >> SATP_ASID_SHIFT)  & SATP_ASID_MASK;
 	asid_bits = fls_long(asid_bits);
+	/* UX608 reports nonzero ASID width but TLB ignores ASIDs. */
+	asid_bits = 0;
 	csr_write(CSR_SATP, old);

 	/*
